From: Hybrid Token-Efficient Routing Agent
Date: 2026
Subject: Add per-task timeout, type-aware routing, and tighter local budget

Three changes to prevent fast-burning tasks from starving the pipeline:

1. PER-TASK HARD TIMEOUT (LOCAL_TASK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, default 45s):
   Wraps local_model.generate() in a threaded timeout. If exceeded, the
   task is treated as "local failed" and escalates to remote immediately.

2. TYPE-AWARE ROUTING (SLOW_TASK_TYPES, default {"sentiment","summarization"}):
   Tasks known to produce slow local inference skip the local model
   entirely and go straight to the remote escalation tier.

3. TIGHTER LOCAL BUDGET:
   Default max_tokens reduced from 256 to 128 so even tasks that do run
   locally consume less wall-clock time.

